{"key":"post-11951081","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>11951081</id>\n<content>There's lots of fucking around in this thread, but most of it is bullshit.&amp;nbsp; If you're just starting out, you'll be fine around the spores.&amp;nbsp; It takes a few years of exposure for your body to start rejecting the spores and making you sick.&amp;nbsp; Once that happens, you'll be stuck putting on a respirator just to check on your crop and you'll not be able to grow indoors at all, at least not where you live.&amp;nbsp; As said above, I get deathly ill from exposure to &lt;i&gt;H ulmarius&lt;/i&gt; spores, and had to give up growing them.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's always best to avoid exposure to the spores before you develop an allergy, if you plan on being around the hobby for very long.&amp;nbsp; In addition, quality of the fruits declines rapidly once they drop spores, so that's another reason to pick prior to or just as the veil breaks.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>11951967</next>\n<prev>11950846</prev>\n<first>11949176</first>\n<last>11951967</last>\n<when>1265171020</when>\n<utime>02/03/10 06:23 AM</utime>\n</post>"}